tegory-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/06/trump-attorney-pence-election-conspiracy-trial" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/06/lampedusa-italy-migrant-boats-sink" target="_blank">Bodies of woman and toddler found after migrant boats sink off Lampedusa - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Italian coastguard says two bodies recovered, amid reports of at least 30 people missing from two vessels that sailed from Tunisia. Two shipwrecks overnight off the southern island of Lampedusa. More than 30 people believed to be missing as of Sunday afternoon in what was described as ‘more tragic news’</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sun, 06 Aug 2023 18:24:37 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/06/lampedusa-italy-migrant-boats-sink" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/06/cosy-dramas-are-killer-tickets-at-the-edinburgh-fringe" target="_blank">Cosy crime dramas are killer tickets at the Edinburgh fringe - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Musical whodunnits and political backstabbing dominate the escapist agenda this year. 2023 is expected to be the year of ‘cosy crime’, when world-weary fringe punters will turn to the comfort and escapism of a whodunit.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sun, 06 Aug 2023 11:00:10 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/06/cosy-dramas-are-killer-tickets-at-the-edinburgh-fringe" target="_blank">Click h