ll article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/06/sir-michael-boyd-obituary" target="_blank">Sir Michael Boyd obituary - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Michael Boyd was appointed artistic director of the Royal Shakespeare Company in 2002. He inherited nothing far short of a shambles when he was appointed. His brilliant but foolhardy predecessor, Adrian Noble, had abandoned the Barbican theatre, leased to the company by the City of London at a peppercorn rent, and run up a deficit of nearly £3m.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sun, 06 Aug 2023 14:18:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/06/sir-michael-boyd-obituary" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2023/aug/06/fergal-keane-bbc-war-correspondent-memoir-the-madness-ptsd" target="_blank">The BBC’s Fergal Keane: ‘The breakdowns get harder to recover from each time’ - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Fergal Keane has been a special correspondent for the BBC for more than 30 years. His career has taken a lasting toll on his mental health, and he's now suffering from acute PTSD. In his memoir The Madness, he goes into greater detail, describing multiple breakdowns, alcoholism, and inherited trauma.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sun, 06 Aug 2023 08:30:06 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2023/aug/06/fergal-keane-bbc-war-correspondent-memoir-the-madness-ptsd" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/06/anita-carey-obituary" target="_blank">Anita Carey obituary - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Anita Carey, 77, has died of breast cancer aged 77. Known for her roles in television comedies, epic drama The Spoils of War and Coronation Street. She switched to soap in 1978 when offered a short run in the soap as a victim of domestic violence.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sun, 06 Aug 2023 16:35:13 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/06/anita-carey-obituary" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/ferries-for-hassle-free-holidays/2023/jun/27/next-stop-spain-how-to-start-your-european-road-trip-on-the-sea" target="_blank">Next stop Spain: how to start your European road trip on the sea - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Katie Nicholson and Ciaran Nicholson have fallen in love with the comfort, ease and flexibility of ferry travel. The couple set sail with Brittany Ferries from the UK to Spain on a new adventure. They are remote working from Spain and Italy on and off for the rest of the year. Good food, great views and comfortable cabin make for a relaxing journey.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 27 Jun 2023 10:33:56 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/ferries-for-hassle-free-holidays/2023/jun/27/next-stop-spain-how-to-start-your-european-road-trip-on-the-sea" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/ferries-for-hassle-free-holidays/2023/jun/15/instaglamour-nerdy-planner-or-freewheeler-take-this-quiz-to-find-out-your-traveller-personality" target="_blank">Instaglamour, nerdy planner or freewheeler? Take this quiz to find out your traveller personality - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Take this quiz to discover what kind of traveller you really are. Some of us just can’t get enough of the likes and follows, while others can't wait to switch off and be at one with a destination. To find out more about hassle-free holidays with Brittany Ferries click here.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 15 Jun 2023 08:41:50 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/ferries-for-hassle-free-holidays/2023/jun/15/instaglamour-nerdy-planner-or-freewheeler-take-this-quiz-to-find-out-your-traveller-personality" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/ferries-for-hassle-free-holidays/2023/jul/04/wine-dine-and-relax-why-taking-the-ferry-is-the-ultimate-in-slow-travel" target="_blank">Wine, dine and relax: why taking the ferry is the ultimate in slow travel - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Take a ferry for your European getaway to avoid airport hassles. Enjoy great food on the way and arrive at your destination feeling fresh and ready to go. From the historic chateaux of the Loire valley to the sunshine glamour of the French Riviera, a holiday to France never fails to delight.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 04 Jul 2023 09:30:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/ferries-for-hassle-free-holidays/2023/jul/04/wine-dine-and-relax-why-taking-the-ferry-is-the-ultimate-in-slow-travel" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div>