ow up a church in Indonesia. He spent seven years in prison after going through a deradicalisation process. After being released from prison, he received support to open a kindergarten.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 25 Jul 2023 09:15:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/24/greece-wildfires-break-out-corfu-thousands-flee-rhodes-blazes-video-report" target="_blank">Greece: wildfires rage on three islands and mainland – video report - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Firefighters struggling to contain 82 wildfires across the country, 64 of which started on Sunday, the hottest day of the summer so far. As well as huge blazes on Rhodes, 19,000 people were forced to flee the island of Rhodes. Wildfires also broke out on Corfu, Corfu and in the northern Peloponnese region.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 24 Jul 2023 13:09:53 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/24/greece-wildfires-break-out-corfu-thousands-flee-rhodes-blazes-video-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/24/spain-faces-political-gridlock-after-national-elections-video-report" target="_blank">Spain faces political gridlock after national elections – video report - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Spain appears to be heading for political gridlock after rightwing parties fail to clinch a decisive victory. Pro-independence Catalan and Basque parties as potential kingmakers. Conservative People's party will be given first attempt at trying to cobble together enough votes to win a prime-ministerial investiture vote.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 24 Jul 2023 12:11:22 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/24/spain-faces-political-gridlock-after-national-elections-video-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">What is supercharging the global heat? – video explainer - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The planet is being hit with a double whammy of global heating in 2023: on top of the rise in global temperature caused by greenhouse gas emissions is an emerging El Niño. This sporadic event is the biggest natural influence on year-to-year weather and adds a further spurt of warmth to an already overheating world.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 16:48:08 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Kids v cars: the campaign to reclaim children's play space on British streets – video - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Playing Out is helping to close streets to cars to reclaim the space on children’s doorsteps. Some experts say a growing mental and physical health crisis could be a result. Families are campaigning for children to have fun outdoors again. The Guardian's Harriet Grant travels to Bristol to meet Playing Out.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 11 Jul 2023 09:30:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Inside the NHS as staff say future hangs in the balance – video - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The NHS was launched in 1948 by Labour MP Aneurin Bevan, inspired in part by the Tredegar Medical Aid Society in his constituency. It has since saved millions of lives and inspired health systems around the world. Seventy-five years on, the Guardian video team was given access to NHS services in south Wales town.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 04 Jul 2023 10:19:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jun/22/what-you-need-to-know-about-the-extreme-heatwave-hitting-our-oceans-video-explainer" target="_blank">What you need to know about the 'extreme' heatwave hitting our oceans – video explainer - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Sea temperatures, particularly off the north-east coast of England and west of Ireland, are several degrees above normal, breaking records for late spring and early summer. The Met Office has said that according to records dating to 1850, global sea surface temperatures in April and May reached an all-time high.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 22 Jun 2023 14:22:05 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jun/22/what-you-need-to-know-about-the-extreme-heatwave-hitting-our-oceans-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/jul/24/tell-us-how-have-you-been-affected-by-wildfires-on-corfu" target="_blank">Greeks: tell us about the aftermath of the wildfires - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> We’d like to hear from local people about the impact of wildfires in regions including Rhodes, Magnesia, Corfu and Evia. Have you been affected? Have you had to evacuate? Has your home or business been damaged? We want to speak with local people on the situation where they are.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 24 Jul 2023 10:03:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/jul/24/tell-us-how-have-you-been-affected-by-wildfires-on-corfu" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/03/uk-workers-over-50-share-your-experience-of-being-a-food-courier" target="_blank">UK workers over 50: share your experience of being a food courier - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Work and pensions secretary, Mel Stride, made the comments during a visit to Deliveroo HQ. Deliveroo has recorded a 62% increase in riders aged over 50 since 2021. We're interested to hear from people aged 50 and over in the UK about what it’s like to work as couriers.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 11:29:13 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/03/uk-workers-over-50-share-your-experience-of-being-a-food-courier" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/03/uk-film-and-tv-workers-how-are-hollywood-strikes-affecting-you" target="_blank">UK film and TV workers: how are Hollywood strikes affecting you? - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> US actors’ union Sag-Aftra joined the Writers Guild of America (WGA) on strike over contract negotiations. Hollywood actors and writers have been on strike at the same time for over six decades. We want to hear how strikes are impacting the UK film and TV industry.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 16:12:39 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/03/uk-film-and-tv-workers-how-are-hollywood-strikes-affecting-you" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/jul/26/people-in-turkey-and-syria-what-has-life-been-like-since-the-february-earthquakes" target="_blank">People in Turkey and Syria: what has life been like since the February earthquakes? - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> We’