nderdogs-bite-back-as-germany-and-brazil-crash-out-womens-football-weekly" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/audio/2023/aug/03/summer-picks-could-the-multiverse-be-real-podcast" target="_blank">Summer picks: could the multiverse be real? | podcast - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> The film Everything Everywhere All at Once won the 2023 Academy Award for Best Picture. Ian Sample spoke to theoretical physicist and philosopher Sean Carroll about why we seem to be drawn to the idea of multiple worlds, and what the science says about how the multiverse might actually work.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 04:00:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/audio/2023/aug/03/summer-picks-could-the-multiverse-be-real-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/03/rishi-sunak-anti-green-gamble-podcast" target="_blank">Rishi Sunak’s anti-green gamble - podcast - The Guardian</a></h2><div class="description"> Rishi Sunak announced new licences for oil and gas exploration in the North Sea this week. It followed full-throated opposition to Labour’s London low-emission zone and renewed zeal for taking on ‘anti-motorist’ councils. Sunak has deftly pivoted to big announcements criticised as anti-environment.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 02:00:31 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/03/rishi-sunak-anti-green-gamble-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a